fix(mcp): Library discovers session MCPs + rail toggles per-session

User feedback (2026-05-22): "github MCP doesn't appear in Library
but is in the session" and "session menu doesn't let you enable/
disable MCP servers".

Two fixes:

1) Library Discovered list now picks up the active session's
   workingDirectory AND merges in the active session's live
   mcp.list. The SDK's server-scoped mcp.discover defaults to
   user-config only — plugin-supplied workspace configs (the
   github MCP via the github plugin) only register against a live
   session, so we have to merge those in explicitly. Source badge
   reads "session" for merged-in entries.

2) Right-rail MCP servers now have a per-server toggle. New
   session-scoped RPC setSessionMcpEnabled wraps
   session.rpc.mcp.enable/disable. Toggle uses status === "disabled"
   as the user-toggled-off state; pending/connecting/error all
   count as enabled. Optimistic flip + reload to surface the real
   SDK status.

Plumbing: 1 new bun RPC threaded through rpc.ts / types.ts /
index.ts / test-server.ts.

Gates: lint clean, 386 bun tests, 64/64 E2E.

Co-authored-by: Copilot <223556219+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>
